<s> Re: 1, 3, 5, There is one, defined recommendation for serializing RDF graphs - its RDF/XML [1].  </s>
<s> The one point of having a recommendation is so everyone can implement one thing, and not many.  </s>
<s> Alternative serialization that encode more information (TriX for the named graphs, some way of using N3 with formulae) is one thing: promoting alternative serialises of RDF just negates the value to clients (samll and large) of having one serialization to deal with.  </s>
<s> Andy [1] OK - it can't serialize every RDF graph [2] [2] Example in case you were wondering: x http://example.org/pred/  </s>
<s> "string" .  </s>
<s> And "yes" it can cause problems.  </s>
<s> I have had a bug report from this - the RDF is created programmatically, it is extracted and serialized.  </s>
